******
[4] Beijing ex Wuhan - Japanese media
Date: Mon 20 Jan 2020
Source: NHK, Japanese media [in Japanese, machine trans., edited]
https://www3.nhk.or.jp/news/html/20200120/k10012251601000.html?utm_int=news_contents_news-main_004


In Wuhan, Hubei Province, China, local authorities have announced that the number of infected cases has increased by 136 to 198, and 3 people have died due to pneumonia suspected of being caused by a new type of coronavirus. In Beijing and southern Guangdong province, 3 new cases of Wuhan were confirmed.

Health officials in Wuhan, Hubei Province said on [Mon 20 Jan 2020] that there were 198 additional cases of pneumonia suspected of being caused by a new type of coronavirus, an increase of 136 over the past 2 days. The number of people who died increased by 1 to 3 and the number of critically ill patients is 9.

In addition, health officials in the Daxing District of Beijing on [Mon 20 Jan 2020] announced that 2 new cases have been confirmed in Beijing, and officials in southern Guangdong have also confirmed that one case has been confirmed in Shenzhen.

All 3 had visited Wuhan, but this is the 1st time Chinese authorities have announced that they have confirmed a patient outside of Wuhan.

In the Chinese government, the national health committee responsible for this matter has urged authorities around the country to step up testing and publish any confirmed infection as soon as possible.

In addition, in China, a major holiday commenced on [24 Jan 2020] of this week in accordance with the Lunar New Year, and as the number of people increases, the Commission has set up a special position during the period to strengthen measures to curb the spread of infection.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[Not surprisingly, there are now reports of cases outside of Wuhan City in China that are being confirmed. Right now, cases are imported cases with a history of travel to Wuhan. It awaits to be seen when local transmission will occur. - Mod.MPP

